body:
While you're at improving ForEach-Object -Parallel please address this:

Doesn't work

```powershell
$OhMy = 'Test'
(1..100) | ForEach-Object -Parallel {
    $Test = $Using:OhMy
    (1..50) | ForEach-Object -Parallel {
        $Test5 = $Using:Test
    }
}
```

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15063294/74090909-8d638d80-4ab1-11ea-8f60-f55be0ae2792.png)


Works:
```powershell
$OhMy = 'Test'
$Test = $null
(1..100) | ForEach-Object -Parallel {
    $Test = $Using:OhMy
    (1..50) | ForEach-Object -Parallel {
        $Test5 = $Using:Test
    }
}
```
